#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn12.60"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.60:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.60:0.2"
msgid "6. Dukkhavagga "
msgstr "6. Suffering "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 60. Nidānasutta → nidāna (paṭiccasamuppāda) suttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn12.60:0.3"
msgid "60. Nidānasutta "
msgstr "60. Sources "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.92, sc1
msgctxt "sn12.60:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kurūsu viharati kammāsadhammaṃ nāma kurūnaṃ nigamo. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Kurus, near the Kuru town named Kammāsadamma. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.60:1.3"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir! It’s amazing, "

msgctxt "sn12.60:1.4"
msgid "Yāva gambhīro cāyaṃ, bhante, paṭiccasamuppādo gambhīrāvabhāso ca, atha ca pana me uttānakuttānako viya khāyatī”ti. "
msgstr "in that this dependent origination is deep and appears deep, yet to me it seems as plain as can be.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn12.60:2.1"
msgid "“Mā hevaṃ, ānanda, mā hevaṃ, ānanda. "
msgstr "“Not so, Ānanda! Not so, Ānanda! "

msgctxt "sn12.60:2.2"
msgid "Gambhīro cāyaṃ, ānanda, paṭiccasamuppādo gambhīrāvabhāso ca. "
msgstr "This dependent origination is deep and appears deep. "

#. VAR: kulagaṇṭhikajātā → guḷāguṇṭhikajātā (bj) | guḷīguṇṭhikajātā (s1-3, km) | guḷigandhikajātā (pts1-2)
#. VAR: muñjapabbajabhūtā → muñjababbajabhūtā (bj)
msgctxt "sn12.60:2.3"
msgid "Etassa, ānanda, dhammassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamayaṃ pajā tantākulakajātā kulagaṇṭhikajātā muñjapabbajabhūtā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ saṃsāraṃ nātivattati. "
msgstr "It is because of not understanding and not penetrating this teaching that this population has become tangled like string, knotted like a ball of thread, and matted like rushes and reeds, and it doesn’t escape the places of loss, the bad places, the underworld, transmigration. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn12.60:3.1"
msgid "Upādāniyesu, ānanda, dhammesu assādānupassino viharato taṇhā pavaḍḍhati. "
msgstr "There are things that are prone to being grasped. When you concentrate on the gratification provided by these things, your craving grows. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:3.2"
msgid "Taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ; "
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:3.3"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo; "
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:3.4"
msgid "bhavapaccayā jāti; "
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:3.5"
msgid "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:3.6"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.93, sc4
msgctxt "sn12.60:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, mahārukkho. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a great tree. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:4.2"
msgid "Tassa yāni ceva mūlāni adhogamāni, yāni ca tiriyaṅgamāni, sabbāni tāni uddhaṃ ojaṃ abhiharanti. "
msgstr "And its roots going downwards and across all draw the sap upwards. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:4.3"
msgid "Evañhi so, ānanda, mahārukkho tadāhāro tadupādāno ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ tiṭṭheyya. "
msgstr "Fueled and sustained by that, the great tree would stand for a long time. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.60:4.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, ānanda, upādāniyesu dhammesu assādānupassino viharato taṇhā pavaḍḍhati. "
msgstr "In the same way, there are things that are prone to being grasped. When you concentrate on the gratification provided by these things, your craving grows. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:4.5"
msgid "Taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ; "
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:4.6"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo … pe … "
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence. … "

msgctxt "sn12.60:4.7"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn12.60:5.1"
msgid "Upādāniyesu, ānanda, dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato taṇhā nirujjhati. "
msgstr "There are things that are prone to being grasped. When you concentrate on the drawbacks of these things, your craving ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:5.2"
msgid "Taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho; "
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:5.3"
msgid "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho … pe … "
msgstr "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. … "

msgctxt "sn12.60:5.4"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn12.60:6.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, mahārukkho. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a great tree. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.2"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya kuddālapiṭakaṃ ādāya. "
msgstr "Then a person comes along with a spade and basket. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.3"
msgid "So taṃ rukkhaṃ mūle chindeyya, mūle chetvā palikhaṇeyya, palikhaṇitvā mūlāni uddhareyya antamaso usīranāḷimattānipi. "
msgstr "They’d cut the tree down at the roots, dig them up, and pull them out, down to the fibers and stems. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.4"
msgid "So taṃ rukkhaṃ khaṇḍākhaṇḍikaṃ chindeyya. "
msgstr "Then they’d split the tree apart, cut up the parts, and chop it into little bits. They’d dry the bits in the wind and sun, burn them with fire, and reduce them to ashes. Then they’d winnow the ashes in a strong wind, or float them away down a swift stream. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.5"
msgid "Khaṇḍākhaṇḍikaṃ chinditvā phāleyya; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.6"
msgid "phāletvā sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ kareyya, sakalikaṃ sakalikaṃ karitvā vātātape visoseyya, vātātape visosetvā agginā ḍaheyya, agginā ḍahetvā masiṃ kareyya, masiṃ karitvā mahāvāte vā ophuṇeyya, nadiyā vā sīghasotāya pavāheyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.7"
msgid "Evañhi so, ānanda, mahārukkho ucchinnamūlo assa tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo. "
msgstr "In this way the great tree is cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.60:6.8"
msgid "Evameva kho, ānanda, upādāniyesu dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato taṇhā nirujjhati. "
msgstr "In the same way, there are things that are prone to being grasped. When you concentrate on the drawbacks of these things, your craving ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.9"
msgid "Taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho; "
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.10"
msgid "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho; "
msgstr "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.11"
msgid "bhavanirodhā jātinirodho; "
msgstr "When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.12"
msgid "jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease. "

msgctxt "sn12.60:6.13"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.60:6.14"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.60:6.15"
msgid "Dukkhavaggo chaṭṭho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn12.60:7.1"
msgid "Parivīmaṃsanupādānaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.60:7.2"
msgid "dve ca saṃyojanāni ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.60:7.3"
msgid "Mahārukkhena dve vuttā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.60:7.4"
msgid "taruṇena ca sattamaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.60:7.5"
msgid "Nāmarūpañca viññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn12.60:7.6"
msgid "nidānena ca te dasāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
